See https://github.com/wildfish/django-star-ratings/blob/develop/star_ratings/templates/star_ratings/widget_base.html#L50 to figure out which elements to hide.

Another approach would be to change the template tag to accept a `template` variable to override the default template path - you could then customise the template each time you used the tag. I'll look at doing that at some point in the next couple of weeks, but we'd welcome a PR if you get to it before me.

